pacing(6)] thread-lg:[--thread-content-margin:--spacing(16)] px-(--thread-content-margin)"><div class="[--thread-content-max-width:40rem] thread-lg:[--thread-content-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col agent-turn" tabindex="-1"><div class="flex max-w-full flex-col grow"><div class="absolute flex h-8 w-3 origin-center items-center justify-center" style="opacity: 0; transform: scale(0);"><div class="bg-token-text-primary h-3 w-3 rounded-full"></div></div><div class="relative my-1 min-h-6"><div class="origin-top-start relative flex flex-col gap-2 overflow-x-clip" style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><div class="relative w-full text-start"><div class="flex w-full flex-row items-start justify-between gap-4 text-start"><button class="flex min-w-0 shrink-1 items-center gap-0.5"><span class="font-medium w-full"><span class="flex items-center gap-1 truncate text-start align-middle text-token-text-secondary hover:text-token-text-primary dark:hover:text-token-text-primary dark:text-[var(--interactive-label-tertiary-default)]" style="opacity: 1;"><div class="truncate">Thought for 27s</div></span></span></button></div></div><div class="max-w-[calc(0.8*var(--thread-content-max-width,40rem))]"></div></div></div><div data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="50c7ea08-9ef0-4287-9c55-7edf80f5888e" dir="auto" class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-1-thinking"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden first:pt-[1px]"><div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full break-words dark markdown-new-styling"><p data-start="0" data-end="269">Here’s a first-cut <strong data-start="19" data-end="43">spec + formal syntax</strong> for a core <em data-start="55" data-end="75">SpherePOP Calculus</em> that we can refine later. I’ll treat it like a small process calculus whose primitive notion is a “sphere” (a boundary object) and “popping” (removing a boundary and re-attaching its contents).</p>
<p data-start="271" data-end="285">I’ll separate:</p>
<ol data-start="287" data-end="535">
<li data-start="287" data-end="339">
<p data-start="290" data-end="339">Informal model (what a sphere is supposed to be).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="340" data-end="393">
<p data-start="343" data-end="393">Abstract syntax (mathematical, for proofs / Lean).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="394" data-end="446">
<p data-start="397" data-end="446">Concrete surface syntax (what code <em data-start="432" data-end="444">looks like</em>).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="447" data-end="483">
<p data-start="450" data-end="483">Static structure / typing sketch.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="484" data-end="535">
<p data-start="487" data-end="535">Operational rules for <code data-start="509" data-end="514">pop</code> and message passing.</p>
</li>
</ol>
<hr data-start="537" data-end="540">
<h2 data-start="542" data-end="562">1. Informal Model</h2>
<p data-start="564" data-end="578"><strong data-start="564" data-end="578">Intuition.</strong></p>
<ul data-start="580" data-end="947">
<li data-start="580" data-end="878">
<p data-start="582" data-end="638">A <em data-start="584" data-end="592">sphere</em> is a <strong data-start="598" data-end="632">named, boundary-forming region</strong> that:</p>
<ul data-start="641" data-end="878">
<li data-start="641" data-end="685">
<p data-start="643" data-end="685">has a <strong data-start="649" data-end="666">local process</strong> running inside it,</p>
</li>
<li data-start="688" data-end="730">
<p data-start="690" data-end="730">exposes a <strong data-start="700" data-end="729">finite interface of ports</strong>,</p>
</li>
<li data-start="733" data-end="773">
<p data-start="735" data-end="773">may reference other spheres by handle,</p>
</li>
<li data-start="776" data-end="878">
<p data-start="778" data-end="878">can be <strong data-start="785" data-end="795">popped</strong>, which dissolves the boundary and splices its inside into the surrounding context.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="880" data-end="947">
<p data-start="882" data-end="947">A <strong data-start="884" data-end="895">program</strong> is a parallel composition of spheres and processes.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="949" data-end="960">Core ideas:</p>
<ul data-start="962" data-end="1357">
<li data-start="962" data-end="1020">
<p data-start="964" data-end="1020"><strong data-start="964" data-end="977">Processes</strong> communicate via <strong data-start="994" data-end="1003">ports</strong> (like channels).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1021" data-end="1152">
<p data-start="1023" data-end="1044">A <strong data-start="1025" data-end="1035">sphere</strong> carries:</p>
<ul data-start="1047" data-end="1152">
<li data-start="1047" data-end="1067">
<p data-start="1049" data-end="1067">an identifier <code data-start="1063" data-end="1066">s</code>,</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1070" data-end="1123">
<p data-start="1072" data-end="1123">an interface <code data-start="1085" data-end="1088">I</code> (ports with directions and types),</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1126" data-end="1152">
<p data-start="1128" data-end="1152">an internal process <code data-start="1148" data-end="1151">P</code>.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="1153" data-end="1357">
<p data-start="1155" data-end="1181">The <strong data-start="1159" data-end="1170"><code data-start="1161" data-end="1168">pop s</code></strong> operation:</p>
<ul data-start="1184" data-end="1357">
<li data-start="1184" data-end="1238">
<p data-start="1186" data-end="1238">is only valid <em data-start="1200" data-end="1223">in the parent context</em> that owns <code data-start="1234" data-end="1237">s</code>,</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1241" data-end="1357">
<p data-start="1243" data-end="1357">removes sphere <code data-start="1258" data-end="1261">s</code> and places its process <code data-start="1285" data-end="1288">P</code> <em data-start="1289" data-end="1302">in parallel</em> with the parent process (subject to interface wiring).</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1359" data-end="1460">You can think of SpherePOP as “π-calculus with explicit local regions that you can erase at runtime”.</p>
<hr data-start="1462" data-end="1465">
<h2 data-start="1467" data-end="1504">2. Abstract Syntax (Core Calculus)</h2>
<p data-start="1506" data-end="1570">We first give a minimal core calculus, ignoring syntactic sugar.</p>
<h3 data-start="1572" data-end="1590">2.1 Basic Sets</h3>
<ul data-start="1592" data-end="1800">
<li data-start="1592" data-end="1625">
<p data-start="1594" data-end="1625"><code data-start="1594" data-end="1599">Var</code> – variables: <code data-start="1613" data-end="1625">x, y, z, …</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="1626" data-end="1661">
<p data-start="1628" data-end="1661"><code data-start="1628" data-end="1634">Name</code> – port names: <code data-start="1649" data-end="1661">p, q, r, …</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="1662" data-end="1704">
<p data-start="1664" data-end="1704"><code data-start="1664" data-end="1669">Sid</code> – sphere identifiers: <code data-start="1692" data-end="1704">s, t, u, …</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="1705" data-end="1733">
<p data-start="1707" data-end="1733"><code data-start="1707" data-end="1712">Lab</code> – record labels: <code data-start="1730" data-end="1733">ℓ</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="1734" data-end="1800">
<p data-start="1736" data-end="1800"><code data-start="1736" data-end="1743">Const</code> – primitive constants: integers, booleans, strings, etc.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1802" data-end="1811">We write:</p>
<ul data-start="1813" data-end="1909">
<li data-start="1813" data-end="1829">
<p data-start="1815" data-end="1829"><code data-start="1815" data-end="1818">v</code> for values</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1830" data-end="1855">
<p data-start="1832" data-end="1855"><code data-start="1832" data-end="1841">P, Q, R</code> for processes</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1856" data-end="1876">
<p data-start="1858" data-end="1876"><code data-start="1858" data-end="1861">I</code> for interfaces</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1877" data-end="1909">
<p data-start="1879" data-end="1909"><code data-start="1879" data-end="1885">Γ, Δ</code> for typing environments</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="1911" data-end="1925">2.2 Values</h3>
<p data-start="1927" data-end="1959">Values are “data”, plus handles:</p>
<ul data-start="1961" data-end="2013">
<li data-start="1961" data-end="2013">
<p data-start="1963" data-end="2013">Variables, constants, records, and sphere handles.</p>
</li>
</ul>
