7 6.136 4.40303 6.07083 4.80371 6.03809C5.14051 6.01057 5.53708 6.00551 6.00391 6.00391C6.00551 5.53708 6.01057 5.14051 6.03809 4.80371C6.0755 4.34588 6.15483 3.94012 6.34668 3.56348L6.46875 3.34473C6.77282 2.84912 7.20856 2.44514 7.72949 2.17969L7.87207 2.11328C8.20855 1.96886 8.56979 1.90385 8.9707 1.87109C9.42091 1.83432 9.978 1.83496 10.667 1.83496H13.5C14.1891 1.83496 14.746 1.83431 15.1963 1.87109C15.6541 1.90851 16.0599 1.98788 16.4365 2.17969L16.6553 2.30176C17.151 2.60585 17.5548 3.04244 17.8203 3.56348L17.8867 3.70606C18.031 4.04235 18.0962 4.40306 18.1289 4.80371C18.1657 5.25395 18.165 5.81091 18.165 6.5V9.33301Z"></path></svg>Copy code</button></div></div></div><div class="overflow-y-auto p-4" dir="ltr"><code class="whitespace-pre! language-text"><span><span>P, Q ::= 0                        (inactive process)
      | P | Q                     (parallel composition)
      | (ν p) P                   (port restriction / fresh port)
      | send p⟨v⟩.P               (send value v on port p then continue as P)
      | recv p(x).P               (receive on p, bind to x then continue)
      | let x = v in P            (value binding)
      | if v then P else Q        (conditional, v should be boolean)
      | sphere s : I [ P ]        (sphere with id s, interface I, body P)
      | pop s . P                 (pop sphere s, then continue as P)
</span></span></code></div></div></pre>
<p data-start="3176" data-end="3182">Notes:</p>
<ul data-start="3184" data-end="3463">
<li data-start="3184" data-end="3278">
<p data-start="3186" data-end="3278"><code data-start="3186" data-end="3206">sphere s : I [ P ]</code> is a <em data-start="3212" data-end="3221">process</em> representing a sphere boundary and its internal process.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3279" data-end="3463">
<p data-start="3281" data-end="3463"><code data-start="3281" data-end="3292">pop s . P</code> is a process that, when executed in a context where a sphere <code data-start="3354" data-end="3374">sphere s : I [ Q ]</code> is present, will dissolve that sphere and replace it with <code data-start="3433" data-end="3440">Q | P</code> (modulo wiring rules).</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="3465" data-end="3535">This is a <strong data-start="3475" data-end="3492">core calculus</strong>; later we can define syntactic sugar like:</p>
<ul data-start="3537" data-end="3661">
<li data-start="3537" data-end="3611">
<p data-start="3539" data-end="3611"><code data-start="3539" data-end="3565">spawn sphere s : I { P }</code> → <code data-start="3568" data-end="3611">(ν internalPorts) sphere s : I [ P ] | P'</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="3612" data-end="3661">
<p data-start="3614" data-end="3661">“methods” / handlers as patterns on <code data-start="3650" data-end="3656">recv</code> etc.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="3663" data-end="3666">
<h2 data-start="3668" data-end="3707">3. Concrete Surface Syntax (Textual)</h2>
<p data-start="3709" data-end="3775">This is what a programmer writes. It desugars into the core above.</p>
<h3 data-start="3777" data-end="3802">3.1 Lexical Structure</h3>
<ul data-start="3804" data-end="4290">
<li data-start="3804" data-end="3965">
<p data-start="3806" data-end="3818">Identifiers:</p>
<ul data-start="3821" data-end="3965">
<li data-start="3821" data-end="3853">
<p data-start="3823" data-end="3853">Variable: <code data-start="3833" data-end="3853">[a-z][A-Za-z0-9_]*</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="3856" data-end="3931">
<p data-start="3858" data-end="3931">Sphere name: same pattern, but in the grammar they appear after <code data-start="3922" data-end="3930">sphere</code>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3934" data-end="3965">
<p data-start="3936" data-end="3965">Port name: same as variables.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="3966" data-end="4140">
<p data-start="3968" data-end="3990">Keywords (reserved):</p>
<p data-start="3994" data-end="4140"><code data-start="3994" data-end="4002">sphere</code>, <code data-start="4004" data-end="4009">pop</code>, <code data-start="4011" data-end="4015">in</code>, <code data-start="4017" data-end="4022">out</code>, <code data-start="4024" data-end="4031">inout</code>, <code data-start="4033" data-end="4038">let</code>, <code data-start="4040" data-end="4044">in</code>, <code data-start="4046" data-end="4050">if</code>, <code data-start="4052" data-end="4058">then</code>, <code data-start="4060" data-end="4066">else</code>, <code data-start="4068" data-end="4074">true</code>, <code data-start="4076" data-end="4083">false</code>, <code data-start="4085" data-end="4091">type</code>, <code data-start="4093" data-end="4099">port</code>, <code data-start="4101" data-end="4104">0</code>, <code data-start="4106" data-end="4111">new</code>, <code data-start="4113" data-end="4119">send</code>, <code data-start="4121" data-end="4127">recv</code>, <code data-start="4129" data-end="4139">parallel</code>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4142" data-end="4219">
<p data-start="4144" data-end="4153">Literals:</p>
<ul data-start="4156" data-end="4219">
<li data-start="4156" data-end="4219">
<p data-start="4158" data-end="4219">integers, floats, strings <code data-start="4184" data-end="4191">"..."</code>, booleans <code data-start="4202" data-end="4208">true</code> / <code data-start="4211" data-end="4218">false</code>.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="4221" data-end="4290">
<p data-start="4223" data-end="4232">Comments:</p>
<ul data-start="4235" data-end="4290">
<li data-start="4235" data-end="4259">
<p data-start="4237" data-end="4259">Line comment: <code data-start="4251" data-end="4259">// ...</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="4262" data-end="4290">
<p data-start="4264" data-end="4290">Block comment: <code data-start="4279" data-end="4290">/* ... */</code></p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="4292" data-end="4322">3.2 Surface Grammar (EBNF)</h3>
<p data-start="4324" data-end="4337"><strong data-start="4324" data-end="4337">Programs:</strong></p>
