</ul>
<p data-start="7852" data-end="8044">You can make <code data-start="7865" data-end="7876">Sphere(I)</code> a type of <code data-start="7887" data-end="7890">s</code> when used as a <em data-start="7906" data-end="7913">value</em>; in this first version, <code data-start="7938" data-end="7941">s</code> is a <em data-start="7947" data-end="7967">process identifier</em> not passed as a value. We can extend it later to first-class sphere handles.</p>
<hr data-start="8046" data-end="8049">
<h2 data-start="8051" data-end="8095">5. Operational Semantics (Selected Rules)</h2>
<p data-start="8097" data-end="8146">We give a standard small-step semantics <code data-start="8137" data-end="8145">P → P'</code>.</p>
<h3 data-start="8148" data-end="8177">5.1 Structural Congruence</h3>
<p data-start="8179" data-end="8222">We extend process equality with usual laws:</p>
<ul data-start="8224" data-end="8357">
<li data-start="8224" data-end="8245">
<p data-start="8226" data-end="8245"><code data-start="8226" data-end="8245">(P | Q) ≡ (Q | P)</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="8246" data-end="8279">
<p data-start="8248" data-end="8279"><code data-start="8248" data-end="8279">(P | (Q | R)) ≡ ((P | Q) | R)</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="8280" data-end="8293">
<p data-start="8282" data-end="8293"><code data-start="8282" data-end="8293">P | 0 ≡ P</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="8294" data-end="8309">
<p data-start="8296" data-end="8309"><code data-start="8296" data-end="8309">(ν p) 0 ≡ 0</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="8310" data-end="8357">
<p data-start="8312" data-end="8357">If <code data-start="8315" data-end="8326">p ∉ fn(Q)</code>: <code data-start="8328" data-end="8357">(ν p) (P | Q) ≡ (ν p) P | Q</code></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="8359" data-end="8389">And treat <code data-start="8369" data-end="8372">≡</code> as a congruence.</p>
<h3 data-start="8391" data-end="8412">5.2 Communication</h3>
<ul data-start="8414" data-end="8658">
<li data-start="8414" data-end="8506">
<p data-start="8416" data-end="8448"><code data-start="8416" data-end="8424">(COMM)</code> (synchronous send/recv)</p>
