e flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col agent-turn" tabindex="-1"><div class="flex max-w-full flex-col grow"><div class="absolute flex h-8 w-3 origin-center items-center justify-center" style="opacity: 0; transform: scale(0);"><div class="bg-token-text-primary h-3 w-3 rounded-full"></div></div><div class="relative my-1 min-h-6"><div class="origin-top-start relative flex flex-col gap-2 overflow-x-clip" style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><div class="relative w-full text-start"><div class="flex w-full flex-row items-start justify-between gap-4 text-start"><button class="flex min-w-0 shrink-1 items-center gap-0.5"><span class="font-medium w-full"><span class="flex items-center gap-1 truncate text-start align-middle text-token-text-secondary hover:text-token-text-primary dark:hover:text-token-text-primary dark:text-[var(--interactive-label-tertiary-default)]" style="opacity: 1;"><div class="truncate">Thought for 30s</div></span></span></button></div></div><div class="max-w-[calc(0.8*var(--thread-content-max-width,40rem))]"></div></div></div><div data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="16d7f666-c70c-42c0-92ae-f9917a4e2224" dir="auto" class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-1-thinking"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden first:pt-[1px]"><div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full break-words dark markdown-new-styling"><p data-start="0" data-end="190">Nice, this version is <em data-start="22" data-end="28">very</em> close to a proper PL-style spec already. Let me take what you wrote and tighten it into something you could literally drop into a paper or implement in Lean/Coq:</p>
<ul data-start="192" data-end="451">
<li data-start="192" data-end="238">
<p data-start="194" data-end="238">make the syntax fully BNF-ish and stratified</p>
</li>
<li data-start="239" data-end="337">
<p data-start="241" data-end="337">separate “process semantics” (discrete events) from “field semantics” (continuous superposition)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="338" data-end="420">
<p data-start="340" data-end="420">make the interference / dissipation rules precise at the level of configurations</p>
</li>
<li data-start="421" data-end="451">
<p data-start="423" data-end="451">give a clean typing judgment</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="453" data-end="545">I’ll treat your text as the <strong data-start="481" data-end="503">intended semantics</strong> and then restate a <strong data-start="523" data-end="544">crisp formal spec</strong>.</p>
<hr data-start="547" data-end="550">
<h2 data-start="552" data-end="575">1. Primitive Domains</h2>
<p data-start="577" data-end="581">Let:</p>
<ul data-start="583" data-end="631">
<li data-start="583" data-end="617">
<p data-start="585" data-end="617"><code data-start="585" data-end="597">Space = ℝⁿ</code> (for fixed <code data-start="609" data-end="616">n ≥ 1</code>)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="618" data-end="631">
<p data-start="620" data-end="631"><code data-start="620" data-end="631">Time  = ℝ</code></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="633" data-end="651">Auxiliary domains:</p>
<ul data-start="653" data-end="899">
<li data-start="653" data-end="724">
<p data-start="655" data-end="724"><code data-start="655" data-end="661">RFun</code> – set of radius-evolution functions<br data-start="697" data-end="700">
<code data-start="702" data-end="724">ρ : Time → ℝ_{\ge 0}</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="726" data-end="805">
<p data-start="728" data-end="805"><code data-start="728" data-end="733">Amp</code> – set of amplitude profiles<br data-start="761" data-end="764">
<code data-start="766" data-end="780">A : Time → ℝ</code> (or ℂ if you want waves)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="807" data-end="899">
<p data-start="809" data-end="899"><code data-start="809" data-end="815">Mode</code> – set of mode identifiers (any countable set, with a monoidal structure <code data-start="888" data-end="891">⋆</code> later).</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="901" data-end="941">We assume a <strong data-start="913" data-end="940">background scalar field</strong>:</p>
<ul data-start="943" data-end="995">
<li data-start="943" data-end="995">
<p data-start="945" data-end="995"><code data-start="945" data-end="968">Φ₀ : Space × Time → ℝ</code> (e.g., background entropy)</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="997" data-end="1000">
<h2 data-start="1002" data-end="1031">2. Pops and Configurations</h2>
<h3 data-start="1033" data-end="1055">2.1 Pop Parameters</h3>
<p data-start="1057" data-end="1088">A <strong data-start="1059" data-end="1076">pop parameter</strong> is a tuple:</p>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>c</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>ρ</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>A</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>μ</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">p = (c, t_0, \rho, A, \mu)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.625em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">p</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">c</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3011em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">0</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">ρ</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">A</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">μ</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span></span>
<p data-start="1124" data-end="1129">with:</p>
<ul data-start="1131" data-end="1269">
<li data-start="1131" data-end="1153">
<p data-start="1133" data-end="1153"><code data-start="1133" data-end="1144">c ∈ Space</code> (center)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1154" data-end="1185">
<p data-start="1156" data-end="1185"><code data-start="1156" data-end="1167">t₀ ∈ Time</code> (initiation time)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1186" data-end="1217">
<p data-start="1188" data-end="1217"><code data-start="1188" data-end="1198">ρ ∈ RFun</code> (radius evolution)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1218" data-end="1249">
<p data-start="1220" data-end="1249"><code data-start="1220" data-end="1229">A ∈ Amp</code> (amplitude profile)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1250" data-end="1269">
<p data-start="1252" data-end="1269"><code data-start="1252" data-end="1262">μ ∈ Mode</code> (mode)</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1271" data-end="1277">Write:</p>
<ul data-start="1279" data-end="1381">
<li data-start="1279" data-end="1296">
<p data-start="1281" data-end="1296"><code data-start="1281" data-end="1296">center(p) = c</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="1297" data-end="1315">
<p data-start="1299" data-end="1315"><code data-start="1299" data-end="1315">start(p)  = t₀</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="1316" data-end="1338">
<p data-start="1318" data-end="1338"><code data-start="1318" data-end="1338">radius_p(t) = ρ(t)</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="1339" data-end="1361">
<p data-start="1341" data-end="1361"><code data-start="1341" data-end="1361">amp_p(t)    = A(t)</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="1362" data-end="1381">
<p data-start="1364" data-end="1381"><code data-start="1364" data-end="1381">mode(p)     = μ</code></p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="1383" data-end="1413">2.2 Spherical Front Kernel</h3>
<p data-start="1415" data-end="1466">Given a pop <code data-start="1427" data-end="1430">p</code>, define its <strong data-start="1443" data-end="1465">front contribution</strong>:</p>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>S</mi><mi>p</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mrow><mo fence="true">{</mo><mtable rowspacing="0.36em" columnalign="left left" columnspacing="1em"><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="false"><mrow><mi>A</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>⋅</mo><mi>δ</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">∥</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>−</mo><mi>c</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">∥</mi><mo>−</mo><mi>ρ</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></mstyle></mtd><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="false"><mrow><mtext>if&nbsp;</mtext><mi>t</mi><mo>≥</mo><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow></mstyle></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="false"><mn>0</mn></mstyle></mtd><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="false"><mrow><mtext>if&nbsp;</mtext><mi>t</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow></mstyle></mtd></mtr></mtable></mrow></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">S_p(x,t) = 
\begin{cases}
A(t) \cdot \delta(\|x - c\| - \rho(t)) &amp; \text{if } t \ge t_0 \\
0 &amp; \text{if } t &lt; t_0
\end{cases}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1.0361em; vertical-align: -0.2861em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.05764em;">S</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.1514em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0576em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">p</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2861em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 3em; vertical-align: -1.25em;"></span><span class="minner"><span class="mopen delimcenter" style="top: 0em;"><span class="delimsizing size4">{</span></span><span class="mord"><span class="mtable"><span class="col-align-l"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 1.69em;"><span style="top: -3.69em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3.008em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">A</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">⋅</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.03785em;">δ</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord">∥</span><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">−</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">c</span><span class="mord">∥</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">−</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">ρ</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mclose">))</span></span></span><span style="top: -2.25em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3.008em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord">0</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 1.19em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="arraycolsep" style="width: 1em;"></span><span class="col-align-l"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 1.69em;"><span style="top: -3.69em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3.008em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">if&nbsp;</span></span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">≥</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3011em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">0</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span style="top: -2.25em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3.008em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">if&nbsp;</span></span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">&lt;</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3011em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">0</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 1.19em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose nulldelimiter"></span></span></span></span></span></span>
<p data-start="1601" data-end="1674">where <code data-start="1607" data-end="1610">δ</code> is the Dirac delta (or a regularized shell kernel in practice).</p>
<h3 data-start="1676" data-end="1714">2.3 Active Pops and Configurations</h3>
<p data-start="1716" data-end="1720">Let:</p>
<ul data-start="1722" data-end="1841">
<li data-start="1722" data-end="1767">
<p data-start="1724" data-end="1767"><code data-start="1724" data-end="1730">Pops</code> be the set of all pops (parameters).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1768" data-end="1841">
<p data-start="1770" data-end="1841">A <strong data-start="1772" data-end="1785">pop store</strong> <code data-start="1786" data-end="1789">Π</code> is a finite multiset of pops: <code data-start="1820" data-end="1840">Π ∈ Multiset(Pops)</code>.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1843" data-end="1866">A <strong data-start="1845" data-end="1862">configuration</strong> is:</p>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">C</mi><mo>=</mo><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>P</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">Π</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\mathcal{C} = (P, \Pi)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.05834em;">C</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.13889em;">P</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord">Π</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span></span>
<ul data-start="1898" data-end="2000">
<li data-start="1898" data-end="1933">
<p data-start="1900" data-end="1933"><code data-start="1900" data-end="1903">P</code> – process term (syntax below)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1934" data-end="2000">
<p data-start="1936" data-end="2000"><code data-start="1936" data-end="1939">Π</code> – multiset of pops that have been emitted and remain active.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="2002" data-end="2065">The <strong data-start="2006" data-end="2023">field induced</strong> by configuration <code data-start="2041" data-end="2049">(P, Π)</code> at time <code data-start="2058" data-end="2061">t</code> is:</p>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant="normal">Φ</mi><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>P</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">Π</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></msub><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>=</mo><msub><mi mathvariant="normal">Φ</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>+</mo><munder><mo>∑</mo><mrow><mi>p</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">Π</mi></mrow></munder><msub><mi>S</mi><mi>p</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">.</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\Phi_{(P,\Pi)}(x,t) = \Phi_0(x,t) + \sum_{p \in \Pi} S_p(x,t).</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1.1052em; vertical-align: -0.3552em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord">Φ</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3448em;"><span style="top: -2.5198em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mopen mtight">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal mtight" style="margin-right: 0.13889em;">P</span><span class="mpunct mtight">,</span><span class="mord mtight">Π</span><span class="mclose mtight">)</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3552em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord">Φ</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3011em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">0</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">+</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 2.4804em; vertical-align: -1.4304em;"></span><span class="mop op-limits"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 1.05em;"><span style="top: -1.8557em; margin-left: 0em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3.05em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">p</span><span class="mrel mtight">∈</span><span class="mord mtight">Π</span></span></span></span><span style="top: -3.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3.05em;"></span><span><span class="mop op-symbol large-op">∑</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 1.4304em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.05764em;">S</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.1514em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0576em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">p</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2861em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mord">.</span></span></span></span></span>
<p data-start="2137" data-end="2196">(This is your denotational semantics in concentrated form.)</p>
<hr data-start="2198" data-end="2201">
<h2 data-start="2203" data-end="2215">3. Syntax</h2>
<p data-start="2217" data-end="2313">We make syntax precise in layers: processes, expressions, conditions, and parameter expressions.</p>
<h3 data-start="2315" data-end="2349">3.1 Identifiers and Basic Sets</h3>
<ul data-start="2351" data-end="2427">
<li data-start="2351" data-end="2381">
<p data-start="2353" data-end="2381">Term variables: <code data-start="2369" data-end="2381">x, y, z, …</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="2382" data-end="2427">
<p data-start="2384" data-end="2427">Process variables (for <code data-start="2407" data-end="2412">fix</code>): <code data-start="2415" data-end="2427">X, Y, Z, …</code></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="2429" data-end="2518">We assume the usual infinite sets of identifiers, with α-equivalence for bound variables.</p>
<h3 data-start="2520" data-end="2539">3.2 Expressions</h3>
<p data-start="2541" data-end="2608">Expressions compute numbers, points, radii, amplitudes, modes, etc.</p>
<p data-start="2610" data-end="2614">BNF:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible!" data-start="2616" data-end="2932"><div class="contain-inline-size rounded-2xl corner-superellipse/1.1 relative bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary"><div class="flex items-center text-token-text-secondary px-4 py-2 text-xs font-sans justify-between h-9 bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary select-none rounded-t-2xl corner-t-superellipse/1.1">bnf</div><div class="sticky top-9"><div class="absolute end-0 bottom-0 flex h-9 items-center pe-2"><div class="bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary text-token-text-secondary flex items-center gap-4 rounded-sm px-2 font-sans text-xs"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-1" aria-label="Copy"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="icon-sm"><path d="M12.668 10.667C12.668 9.95614 12.668 9.46258 12.6367 9.0791C12.6137 8.79732 12.5758 8.60761 12.5244 8.46387L12.4688 8.33399C12.3148 8.03193 12.0803 7.77885 11.793 7.60254L11.666 7.53125C11.508 7.45087 11.2963 7.39395 10.9209 7.36328C10.5374 7.33197 10.0439 7.33203 9.33301 7.33203H6.5C5.78896 7.33203 5.29563 7.33195 4.91211 7.36328C4.63016 7.38632 4.44065 7.42413 4.29688 7.47559L4.16699 7.53125C3.86488 7.68518 3.61186 7.9196 3.43555 8.20703L3.36524 8.33399C3.28478 8.49198 3.22795 8.70352 3.19727 9.0791C3.16595 9.46259 3.16504 9.95611 3.16504 10.667V13.5C3.16504 14.211 3.16593 14.7044 3.19727 15.0879C3.22797 15.4636 3.28473 15.675 3.36524 15.833L3.43555 15.959C3.61186 16.2466 3.86474 16.4807 4.16699 16.6348L4.29688 16.6914C4.44063 16.7428 4.63025 16.7797 4.91211 16.8027C5.29563 16.8341 5.78896 16.835 6.5 16.835H9.33301C10.0439 16.835 10.5374 16.8341 10.9209 16.8027C11.2965 16.772 11.508 16.7152 11.666 16.6348L11.793 16.5645C12.0804 16.3881 12.3148 16.1351 12.4688 15.833L12.5244 15.7031C12.5759 15.5594 12.6137 15.3698 12.6367 15.0879C12.6681 14.7044 12.668 14.211 12.668 13.5V10.667ZM13.998 12.665C14.4528 12.6634 14.8011 12.6602 15.0879 12.6367C15.4635 12.606 15.675 12.5492 15.833 12.4688L