 6.136 4.40303 6.07083 4.80371 6.03809C5.14051 6.01057 5.53708 6.00551 6.00391 6.00391C6.00551 5.53708 6.01057 5.14051 6.03809 4.80371C6.0755 4.34588 6.15483 3.94012 6.34668 3.56348L6.46875 3.34473C6.77282 2.84912 7.20856 2.44514 7.72949 2.17969L7.87207 2.11328C8.20855 1.96886 8.56979 1.90385 8.9707 1.87109C9.42091 1.83432 9.978 1.83496 10.667 1.83496H13.5C14.1891 1.83496 14.746 1.83431 15.1963 1.87109C15.6541 1.90851 16.0599 1.98788 16.4365 2.17969L16.6553 2.30176C17.151 2.60585 17.5548 3.04244 17.8203 3.56348L17.8867 3.70606C18.031 4.04235 18.0962 4.40306 18.1289 4.80371C18.1657 5.25395 18.165 5.81091 18.165 6.5V9.33301Z"></path></svg>Copy code</button></div></div></div><div class="overflow-y-auto p-4" dir="ltr"><code class="whitespace-pre! language-bnf"><span>P ::= 0                          -- null process
    | pop(PopExpr)               -- emit a spherepop
    | P | P                      -- parallel composition
    | P ; P                      -- sequential composition
    | let x = E in P             -- binding
    | if C then P else P         -- conditional
    | fix X . P                  -- recursion in X
    | X                          -- process variable
</span></code></div></div></pre>
<hr data-start="4408" data-end="4411">
<h2 data-start="4413" data-end="4440">4. Structural Congruence</h2>
<p data-start="4442" data-end="4515">We define structural congruence <code data-start="4474" data-end="4477">≡</code> as the smallest congruence such that:</p>
<ol data-start="4517" data-end="4822">
<li data-start="4517" data-end="4604">
<p data-start="4520" data-end="4533"><strong data-start="4520" data-end="4533">Parallel:</strong></p>
<ul data-start="4537" data-end="4604">
<li data-start="4537" data-end="4554">
<p data-start="4539" data-end="4554"><code data-start="4539" data-end="4554">P | Q ≡ Q | P</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="4558" data-end="4587">
<p data-start="4560" data-end="4587"><code data-start="4560" data-end="4587">(P | Q) | R ≡ P | (Q | R)</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="4591" data-end="4604">
<p data-start="4593" data-end="4604"><code data-start="4593" data-end="4604">P | 0 ≡ P</code></p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="4606" data-end="4674">
<p data-start="4609" data-end="4624"><strong data-start="4609" data-end="4624">Sequential:</strong></p>
<ul data-start="4628" data-end="4674">
<li data-start="4628" data-end="4657">
<p data-start="4630" data-end="4657"><code data-start="4630" data-end="4657">(P ; Q) ; R ≡ P ; (Q ; R)</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="4661" data-end="4674">
<p data-start="4663" data-end="4674"><code data-start="4663" data-end="4674">0 ; P ≡ P</code></p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="4676" data-end="4739">
<p data-start="4679" data-end="4702"><strong data-start="4679" data-end="4702">Fixpoint unfolding:</strong></p>
<ul data-start="4706" data-end="4739">
<li data-start="4706" data-end="4739">
<p data-start="4708" data-end="4739"><code data-start="4708" data-end="4739">fix X . P ≡ P[X := fix X . P]</code></p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="4741" data-end="4822">
<p data-start="4744" data-end="4822"><strong data-start="4744" data-end="4761">α-equivalence</strong> for bound variables (<code data-start="4783" data-end="4786">x</code>) and bound process variables (<code data-start="4817" data-end="4820">X</code>).</p>
</li>
</ol>
<p data-start="4824" data-end="4892">We always consider processes up to <code data-start="4859" data-end="4862">≡</code> in the operational semantics.</p>
<hr data-start="4894" data-end="4897">
<h2 data-start="4899" data-end="4926">5. Operational Semantics</h2>
<p data-start="4928" data-end="4986">We use a <strong data-start="4937" data-end="4967">labelled transition system</strong> on configurations:</p>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>P</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">Π</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mover><mo stretchy="true" minsize="3.0em">→</mo><mpadded width="+0.6em" lspace="0.3em"><mi>α</mi></mpadded></mover><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msup><mi>P</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup><mo separator="true">,</mo><msup><mi mathvariant="normal">Π</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">(P, \Pi) \xrightarrow{\alpha} (P', \Pi')</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1.1734em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.13889em;">P</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord">Π</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel x-arrow"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.9234em;"><span style="top: -3.322em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight x-arrow-pad"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight" style="margin-right: 0.0037em;">α</span></span></span></span><span class="svg-align" style="top: -2.689em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="hide-tail" style="height: 0.522em; min-width: 1.469em;"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="400em" height="0.522em" viewBox="0 0 400000 522" preserveAspectRatio="xMaxYMin slice"><path d="M0 241v40h399891c-47.3 35.3-84 78-110 128
