<p data-start="5683" data-end="5711">where <code data-start="5689" data-end="5692">⊎</code> is multiset union.</p>
<h3 data-start="5713" data-end="5743">5.2 Sequential Composition</h3>
<p data-start="5745" data-end="5884">We treat <code data-start="5754" data-end="5757">;</code> as “run P to completion, then run Q”. At the process-calculus level we capture contact points at pops and internal reductions.</p>
<p data-start="5886" data-end="5913">We define small-step rules:</p>
<ol data-start="5915" data-end="6146">
<li data-start="5915" data-end="6029">
<p data-start="5918" data-end="5937"><strong data-start="5918" data-end="5937">Left reduction:</strong></p>
<p data-start="5942" data-end="5973">If <code data-start="5945" data-end="5966">(P, Π) →_α (P', Π')</code>, then:</p>
