<hr data-start="6954" data-end="6957">
<h2 data-start="6959" data-end="7020">6. Field Evolution, Propagation, Interference, Dissipation</h2>
<p data-start="7022" data-end="7112">So far, transitions only manipulate <code data-start="7058" data-end="7066">(P, Π)</code>. The <strong data-start="7072" data-end="7081">field</strong> is a function of <code data-start="7099" data-end="7102">Π</code> and time:</p>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant="normal">Φ</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">Π</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>=</mo><msub><mi mathvariant="normal">Φ</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>+</mo><munder><mo>∑</mo><mrow><mi>p</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">Π</mi></mrow></munder><msub><mi>S</mi><mi>p</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">.</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\Phi_{Π}(x,t) = \Phi_0(x,t) + \sum_{p \in Π} S_p(x,t).</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord">Φ</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3283em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mtight">Π</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord">Φ</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3011em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">0</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">+</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 2.4804em; vertical-align: -1.4304em;"></span><span class="mop op-limits"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 1.05em;"><span style="top: -1.8557em; margin-left: 0em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3.05em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">p</span><span class="mrel mtight">∈</span><span class="mord mtight">Π</span></span></span></span><span style="top: -3.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3.05em;"></span><span><span class="mop op-symbol large-op">∑</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 1.4304em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.05764em;">S</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.1514em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0576em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">p</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2861em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mord">.</span></span></span></span></span>
<p data-start="7176" data-end="7240">You can model propagation / interference in two equivalent ways:</p>
<ol data-start="7242" data-end="7440">
<li data-start="7242" data-end="7358">
<p data-start="7245" data-end="7358"><strong data-start="7245" data-end="7269">Purely denotational:</strong> <code data-start="7270" data-end="7273">Π</code> is static after emission; all propagation/interference is encoded directly in <code data-start="7352" data-end="7357">S_p</code>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="7359" data-end="7440">
<p data-start="7362" data-end="7440"><strong data-start="7362" data-end="7384">Dynamic pop store:</strong> <code data-start="7385" data-end="7388">Π</code> evolves over time, with rules for merging pops etc.</p>
</li>
</ol>
<p data-start="7442" data-end="7522">Since your spec mentions <em data-start="7467" data-end="7480">merged pops</em> and <em data-start="7485" data-end="7505">interference modes</em>, I’ll adopt (2).</p>
<h3 data-start="7524" data-end="7563">6.1 Time Evolution of the Pop Store</h3>
<p data-start="7565" data-end="7619">We define a <strong data-start="7577" data-end="7604">time-evolution operator</strong> on pop stores:</p>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant="script">E</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">Δ</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msub><mo>:</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">Π</mi><mo>↦</mo><msup><mi mathvariant="normal">Π</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\mathcal{E}_{\Delta t} : \Pi \mapsto \Pi'</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8333em; vertical-align: -0.15em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.08944em;">E</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3283em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0894em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mtight">Δ</span><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">:</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6943em; vertical-align: -0.011em;"></span><span class="mord">Π</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">↦</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8019em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord">Π</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.8019em;"><span style="top: -3.113em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mtight">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>
<p data-start="7670" data-end="7817">capturing propagation and interference between times <code data-start="7723" data-end="7726">t</code> and <code data-start="7731" data-end="7739">t + Δt</code>. Program transitions are instantaneous compared to this continuous evolution.</p>
<p data-start="7819" data-end="7907">We <em data-start="7822" data-end="7830">do not</em> express <code data-start="7839" data-end="7848">𝔈_{Δt}</code> as process-step rules, but as a separate dynamical system:</p>
<ul data-start="7909" data-end="8263">
<li data-start="7909" data-end="7984">
<p data-start="7911" data-end="7984"><strong data-start="7911" data-end="7927">Propagation:</strong> each <code data-start="7933" data-end="7940">p ∈ Π</code> has radius <code data-start="7952" data-end="7960">ρ_p(t)</code> and amplitude <code data-start="7975" data-end="7983">A_p(t)</code>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="7985" data-end="8093">
<p data-start="7987" data-end="8028"><strong data-start="7987" data-end="8003">Dissipation:</strong> amplitude evolves, e.g.:</p>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>p</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>↦</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>p</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">Δ</mi><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>p</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>−</mo><mi>λ</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">Δ</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">A_p(t) \mapsto A_p(t + Δt) = A_p(t) e^{-\lambda Δt}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1.0361em; vertical-align: -0.2861em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">A</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.1514em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">p</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2861em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">↦</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1.0361em; vertical-align: -0.2861em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">A</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.1514em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">p</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2861em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">+</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord">Δ</span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1.1852em; vertical-align: -0.2861em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">A</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.1514em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">p</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2861em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">e</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.8991em;"><span style="top: -3.113em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mtight">−</span><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">λ</span><span class="mord mtight">Δ</span><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>
</li>
<li data-start="8095" data-end="8263">
<p data-start="8097" data-end="8263"><strong data-start="8097" data-end="8122">Interference / merge:</strong> when two pops <code data-start="8137" data-end="8145">p₁, p₂</code> satisfy some <strong data-start="8159" data-end="8184">interaction condition</strong> (e.g., their shells intersect), they can be replaced by a <strong data-start="8243" data-end="8257">merged pop</strong> <code data-start="8258" data-end="8262">p₃</code>.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h4 data-start="8265" data-end="8290">6.1.1 Merge Operator</h4>
<p data-start="8292" data-end="8420">Let <code data-start="8296" data-end="8324">p₁ = (c₁, t₀₁, ρ₁, A₁, μ₁)</code> and <code data-start="8329" data-end="8357">p₂ = (c₂, t₀₂, ρ₂, A₂, μ₂)</code>. Suppose an interaction event is detected at time <code data-start="8408" data-end="8411">t</code>. Define:</p>
<ul data-start="8422" data-end="8544">
<li data-start="8422" data-end="8456">
<p data-start="8424" data-end="8456">radii <code data-start="8430" data-end="8442">R₁ = ρ₁(t)</code>, <code data-start="8444" data-end="8456">R₂ = ρ₂(t)</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="8457" data-end="8544">
<p data-start="8459" data-end="8544">angle <code data-start="8465" data-end="8468">θ</code> between directions (if defined; in a symmetric model you can take <code data-start="8535" data-end="8542">θ = 0</code>).</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="8546" data-end="8593">Define merged parameters (one possible choice):</p>
<ul data-start="8595" data-end="8998">
<li data-start="8595" data-end="8675">
<p data-start="8597" data-end="8675"><code data-start="8597" data-end="8601">c₃</code> – some function of <code data-start="8621" data-end="8631">(c₁, c₂)</code> (e.g., barycenter or locus of intersection)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="8676" data-end="8687">
<p data-start="8678" data-end="8687"><code data-start="8678" data-end="8687">t₀₃ = t</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="8688" data-end="8845">
<p data-start="8690" data-end="8728"><code data-start="8690" data-end="8694">ρ₃</code> – radius evolution determined by:</p>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><msubsup><mi>R</mi><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>=</mo><msubsup><mi>R</mi><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>+</mo><msubsup><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mi>cos</mi><mo>⁡</mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">R_3^2(t) = R_1^2(t) + R_2^2(t) + 2 R_1(t) R_2(t) \cos \theta</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1.1141em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.00773em;">R</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.8641em;"><span style="top: -2.453em; margin-left: -0.0077em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">3</span></span></span><span style="top: -3.113em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">2</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.247em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1.1141em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.00773em;">R</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.8641em;"><span style="top: -2.453em; margin-left: -0.0077em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">1</span></span></span><span style="top: -3.113em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">2</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.247em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">+</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1.1141em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.00773em;">R</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.8641em;"><span style="top: -2.453em; margin-left: -0.0077em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">2</span></span></span><span style="top: -3.113em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">2</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.247em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">+</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord">2</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.00773em;">R</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3011em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0077em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">1</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.00773em;">R</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3011em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0077em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">2</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mop">cos</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.02778em;">θ</span></span></span></span></span>
<p data-start="8806" data-end="8845">or any physically motivated combinator.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="8847" data-end="8916">
<p data-start="8849" data-end="8916"><code data-start="8849" data-end="8872">A₃(t) = A₁(t) + A₂(t)</code> (or another linear / nonlinear combination)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="8917" data-end="8998">
<p data-start="8919" data-end="8998"><code data-start="8919" data-end="8933">μ₃ = μ₁ ⋆ μ₂</code> where <code data-start="8940" data-end="8964">⋆ : Mode × Mode → Mode</code> is a user-given monoid operation.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="9000" data-end="9007">Define:</p>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>p</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">m</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">e</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">r</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">g</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">e</mi></mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mi>p</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo separator="true">,</mo><msub><mi>p</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">.</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">p_3 = \mathrm{merge}(p_1, p_2, t).</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.625em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">p</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3011em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">3</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathrm">merge</span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">p</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3011em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">1</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">p</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3011em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">2</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mord">.</span></span></span></span></span>
<p data-start="9051" data-end="9094">Then pop-store evolution may include steps:</p>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">Π</mi><mo>⇝</mo><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">Π</mi><mo>∖</mo><mo stretchy="false">{</mo><msub><mi>p</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo separator="true">,</mo><msub><mi>p</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo stretchy="false">}</mo><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>⊎</mo><mo stretchy="false">{</mo><msub><mi>p</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo stretchy="false">}</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">.</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\Pi \rightsquigarrow (\Pi \setminus \{p_1,p_2\}) ⊎ \{p_3\}.</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord">Π</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel amsrm">⇝</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord">Π</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">∖</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mopen">{</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">p</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3011em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">1</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">p</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3011em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">2</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose">})</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">⊎</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mopen">{</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">p</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3011em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">3</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose">}</span><span class="mord">.</span></span></span></span></span>
<p data-start="9163" data-end="9231">You can axiomatize <code data-start="9182" data-end="9189">merge</code> and the interaction condition separately.</p>
<h3 data-start="9233" data-end="9260">6.2 Putting It Together</h3>
<p data-start="9262" data-end="9301">A <strong data-start="9264" data-end="9285">full system state</strong> is <code data-start="9289" data-end="9300">(P, Π, t)</code>.</p>
<p data-start="9303" data-end="9336">There are two kinds of evolution:</p>
<ol data-start="9338" data-end="9638">
<li data-start="9338" data-end="9469">
<p data-start="9341" data-end="9385"><strong data-start="9341" data-end="9366">Discrete process step</strong> (no time advance):</p>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>P</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">Π</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mover><mo stretchy="true" minsize="3.0em">→</mo><mpadded width="+0.6em" lspace="0.3em"><mi>α</mi></mpadded></mover><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msup><mi>P</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup><mo separator="true">,</mo><msup><mi mathvariant="normal">Π</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">(P, Π, t) \xrightarrow{\alpha} (P', Π', t)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1.1734em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.13889em;">P</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord">Π</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel x-arrow"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.9234em;"><span style="top: -3.322em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight x-arrow-pad"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight" style="margin-right: 0.0037em;">α</span></span></span></span><span class="svg-align" style="top: -2.689em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="hide-tail" style="height: 0.522em; min-width: 1.469em;"><svg xmlns="h