<p data-start="10046" data-end="10066">Typing environments:</p>
<ul data-start="10068" data-end="10180">
<li data-start="10068" data-end="10103">
<p data-start="10070" data-end="10103"><code data-start="10070" data-end="10073">Γ</code> maps term variables to types.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="10104" data-end="10180">
<p data-start="10106" data-end="10180">Process variables can be tracked in a separate environment <code data-start="10165" data-end="10168">Δ</code> if desired.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="10182" data-end="10213">Selected typing rules (sketch):</p>
<h3 data-start="10215" data-end="10234">7.1 Expressions</h3>
<ul data-start="10236" data-end="10564">
<li data-start="10236" data-end="10409">
<p data-start="10238" data-end="10274">Constants and operators as expected:</p>
<ul data-start="10278" data-end="10409">
<li data-start="10278" data-end="10294">
<p data-start="10280" data-end="10294"><code data-start="10280" data-end="10294">Γ ⊢ r : Real</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="10297" data-end="10314">
<p data-start="10299" data-end="10314"><code data-start="10299" data-end="10314">Γ ⊢ c : Point</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="10317" data-end="10333">
<p data-start="10319" data-end="10333"><code data-start="10319" data-end="10333">Γ ⊢ μ : Mode</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="10336" data-end="10409">
<p data-start="10338" data-end="10409">If <code data-start="10341" data-end="10356">Γ ⊢ E₁ : Real</code> and <code data-start="10361" data-end="10376">Γ ⊢ E₂ : Real</code>, then <code data-start="10383" data-end="10403">Γ ⊢ E₁ + E₂ : Real</code>, etc.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="10411" data-end="10487">
<p data-start="10413" data-end="10424">Radius fun:</p>
<ul data-start="10428" data-end="10487">
<li data-start="10428" data-end="10487">
<p data-start="10430" data-end="10487">If <code data-start="10433" data-end="10457">Γ, t : Real ⊢ E : Real</code>, then <code data-start="10464" data-end="10486">Γ ⊢ λt.E : RadiusFun</code>.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="10489" data-end="10564">
<p data-start="10491" data-end="10501">Amplitude:</p>
<ul data-start="10505" data-end="10564">
<li data-start="10505" data-end="10564">
<p data-start="10507" data-end="10564">If <code data-start="10510" data-end="10534">Γ, t : Real ⊢ E : Real</code>, then <code data-start="10541" data-end="10563">Γ ⊢ λt.E : Amplitude</code>.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="10566" data-end="10588">7.2 Pop Parameters</h3>
<p data-start="10590" data-end="10593">If:</p>
<ul data-start="10595" data-end="10719">
<li data-start="10595" data-end="10616">
<p data-start="10597" data-end="10616"><code data-start="10597" data-end="10616">Γ ⊢ E_c   : Point</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="10617" data-end="10637">
<p data-start="10619" data-end="10637"><code data-start="10619" data-end="10637">Γ ⊢ E_t0  : Real</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="10638" data-end="10666">
<p data-start="10640" data-end="10666"><code data-start="10640" data-end="10666">Γ ⊢ RFunExpr : RadiusFun</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="10667" data-end="10695">
<p data-start="10669" data-end="10695"><code data-start="10669" data-end="10695">Γ ⊢ AmpExpr  : Amplitude</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="10696" data-end="10719">
<p data-start="10698" data-end="10719"><code data-start="10698" data-end="10719">Γ ⊢ ModeExpr : Mode</code></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="10721" data-end="10726">then:</p>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">Γ</mi><mo>⊢</mo><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mi>E</mi><mi>c</mi></msub><mo separator="true">,</mo><msub><mi>E</mi><mrow><mi>t</mi><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>R</mi><mi>F</mi><mi>u</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>E</mi><mi>x</mi><mi>p</mi><mi>r</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>A</mi><mi>m</mi><mi>p</mi><mi>E</mi><mi>x</mi><mi>p</mi><mi>r</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>M</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>E</mi><mi>x</mi><mi>p</mi><mi>r</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>:</mo><mi>P</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>p</mi><mi>P</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>m</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">.</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">Γ ⊢ (E_c, E_{t0}, RFunExpr, AmpExpr, ModeExpr) : PopParam.</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6944em;"></span><span class="mord">Γ</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">⊢</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.05764em;">E</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.1514em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0576em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">c</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.05764em;">E</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3011em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0576em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span><span class="mord mtight">0</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.13889em;">RF</span><span class="mord mathnormal">u</span><span class="mord mathnormal">n</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.05764em;">E</span><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="mord mathnormal">p</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.02778em;">r</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">A</span><span class="mord mathnormal">m</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.05764em;">pE</span><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="mord mathnormal">p</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.02778em;">r</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.10903em;">M</span><span class="mord mathnormal">o</span><span class="mord mathnormal">d</span><span class="mord mathnormal">e</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.05764em;">E</span><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="mord mathnormal">p</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.02778em;">r</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">:</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8778em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.13889em;">P</span><span class="mord mathnormal">o</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.13889em;">pP</span><span class="mord mathnormal">a</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.02778em;">r</span><span class="mord mathnormal">am</span><span class="mord">.</span></span></span></span></span>
<h3 data-start="10794" data-end="10811">7.3 Processes</h3>
<ul data-start="10813" data-end="11419">
<li data-start="10813" data-end="10846">
<p data-start="10815" data-end="10825"><code data-start="10815" data-end="10825">(T-Null)</code></p>
<p data-start="10829" data-end="10846"><code data-start="10829" data-end="10846">Γ ⊢ 0 : Process</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="10848" data-end="10929">
<p data-start="10850" data-end="10859"><code data-start="10850" data-end="10859">(T-Pop)</code></p>
<p data-start="10863" data-end="10896">If <code data-start="10866" data-end="10890">Γ ⊢ PopExpr : PopParam</code> then:</p>
<p data-start="10900" data-end="10929"><code data-start="10900" data-end="10928">Γ ⊢ pop(PopExpr) : Process</code>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="10931" data-end="11021">
<p data-start="10933" data-end="10942"><code data-start="10933" data-end="10942">(T-Par)</code></p>
<p data-start="10946" data-end="10995">If <code data-start="10949" data-end="10966">Γ ⊢ P : Process</code> and <code data-start="10971" data-end="10988">Γ ⊢ Q : Process</code>, then:</p>
<p data-start="10999" data-end="11021"><code data-start="10999" data-end="11020">Γ ⊢ P | Q : Process</code>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="11023" data-end="11113">
<p data-start="11025" data-end="11034"><code data-start="11025" data-end="11034">(T-Seq)</code></p>
<p data-start="11038" data-end="11087">If <code data-start="11041" data-end="11058">Γ ⊢ P : Process</code> and <code data-start="11063" data-end="11080">Γ ⊢ Q : Process</code>, then:</p>
<p data-start="11091" data-end="11113"><code data-start="11091" data-end="11112">Γ ⊢ P ; Q : Process</code>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="11115" data-end="11230">
<p data-start="11117" data-end="11125"><code data-start="11117" data-end="11125">(T-If)</code></p>
<p data-start="11129" data-end="11191">If <code data-start="11132" data-end="11146">Γ ⊢ C : Bool</code>, <code data-start="11148" data-end="11165">Γ ⊢ P : Process</code>, <code data-start="11167" data-end="11184">Γ ⊢ Q : Process</code>, then:</p>
<p data-start="11195" data-end="11230"><code data-start="11195" data-end="11229">Γ ⊢ if C then P else Q : Process</code>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="11232" data-end="11332">
<p data-start="11234" data-end="11243"><code data-start="11234" data-end="11243">(T-Let)</code></p>
<p data-start="11247" data-end="11297">If <code data-start="11250" data-end="11261">Γ ⊢ E : τ</code> and <code data-start="11266" data-end="11290">Γ, x : τ ⊢ P : Process</code>, then:</p>
<p data-start="11301" data-end="11332"><code data-start="11301" data-end="11331">Γ ⊢ let x = E in P : Process</code>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="11334" data-end="11419">
<p data-start="11336" data-end="11345"><code data-start="11336" data-end="11345">(T-Fix)</code></p>
<p data-start="11349" data-end="11389">If <code data-start="11352" data-end="11382">Γ, X : Process ⊢ P : Process</code>, then:</p>
<p data-start="11393" data-end="11419"><code data-start="11393" data-end="11418">Γ ⊢ fix X . P : Process</code>.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="11421" data-end="11424">
<h2 data-start="11426" data-end="11461">8. Meta-Properties (as Theorems)</h2>
<p data-start="11463" data-end="11522">With the above, the properties you listed can be stated as:</p>
<ol data-start="11524" data-end="12678">
<li data-start="11524" data-end="11746">
<p data-start="11527" data-end="11621"><strong data-start="11527" data-end="11560">Deterministic field evolution</strong> (given deterministic <code data-start="11582" data-end="11588">RFun</code>, <code data-start="11590" data-end="11595">Amp</code>, <code data-start="11597" data-end="11604">merge</code>, and <code data-start="11610" data-end="11619">𝔈_{Δt}</code>):</p>
<ul data-start="11625" data-end="11746">
<li data-start="11625" data-end="11746">
<p data-start="11627" data-end="11746">For fixed initial <code data-start="11645" data-end="11659">(P₀, Π₀, t₀)</code> and a schedule of process steps, the function <code data-start="11706" data-end="11722">(x,t) ↦ Φ(x,t)</code> is uniquely determined.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="11748" data-end="11936">
<p data-start="11751" data-end="11792"><strong data-start="11751" data-end="11792">Confluence for non-destructive modes:</strong></p>
<ul data-start="11796" data-end="11936">
<li data-start="11796" data-end="11936">
<p data-start="11798" data-end="11936">If <code data-start="11801" data-end="11804">⋆</code> and <code data-start="11809" data-end="11816">merge</code> are commutative and associative and <code data-start="11853" data-end="11862">𝔈_{Δt}</code> is confluent, different interleavings of pop merges yield the same field.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="11938" data-end="12101">
<p data-start="11941" data-end="11975"><strong data-start="11941" data-end="11975">Locality / finite propagation:</strong></p>
<ul data-start="11979" data-end="12101">
<li data-start="11979" data-end="12101">
<p data-start="11981" data-end="12101">If each <code data-start="11989" data-end="11995">ρ(t)</code> is Lipschitz and bounded by a finite speed <code data-start="12039" data-end="12046">v_max</code>, then support of <code data-start="12064" data-end="12069">S_p</code> grows at most at speed <code data-start="12093" data-end="12100">v_max</code>.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="12103" data-end="12240">
<p data-start="12106" data-end="12123"><strong data-start="12106" data-end="12123">Energy bound:</strong></p>
<ul data-start="12127" data-end="12240">
<li data-start="12127" data-end="12240">
<p data-start="12129" data-end="12240">If each amplitude profile satisfies e.g. <code data-start="12170" data-end="12189">∫ |A_p(t)| dt &lt; ∞</code>, then total integrated amplitude of <code data-start="12226" data-end="12229">Φ</code> is finite.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="12242" data-end="12678">
<p data-start="12245" data-end="12266"><strong data-start="12245" data-end="12266">Compositionality:</strong></p>
<ul data-start="12270" data-end="12678">
<li data-start="12270" data-end="12678">
<p data-start="12272" data-end="12369">For processes <code data-start="12286" data-end="12289">P</code> and <code data-start="12294" data-end="12297">Q</code>, the denotation is compatible with parallel and sequential composition:</p>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">⟦</mo><mi>P</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">∣</mi><mi>Q</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">⟧</mo><mo>=</mo><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">⟦</mo><mi>P</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">⟧</mo><mo>⊕</mo><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">⟦</mo><mi>Q</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">⟧</mo><mo separator="true">,</mo><mspace width="1em"></mspace><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">⟦</mo><mi>P</mi><mo separator="true">;</mo><mi>Q</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">⟧</mo><mo>=</mo><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">⟦</mo><mi>Q</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">⟧</mo><mo>∘</mo><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">⟦</mo><mi>P</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">⟧</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\llbracket P | Q \rrbracket = \llbracket P \rrbracket \oplus \llbracket Q \rrbracket,
\quad
\llbracket P ; Q \rrbracket = \llbracket Q \rrbracket \circ \llbracket P \rrbracket</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mopen"><span class="mopen">[</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: -0.1778em;"></span><span class="mopen">[</span></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.13889em;">P</span><span class="mord">∣</span><span class="mord mathnormal">Q</span><span class="mclose"><span class="mclose">]</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: -0.1778em;"></span><span class="mclose">]</span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mopen"><span class="mopen">[</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: -0.1778em;"></span><span class="mopen">[</span></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.13889em;">P</span><span class="mclose"><span class="mclose">]</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: -0.1778em;"></span><span class="mclose">]</span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">⊕</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mopen"><span class="mopen">[</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: -0.1778em;"></span><span class="mopen">[</span></span><span class="mord mathnormal">Q</span><span class="mclose"><span class="mclose">]</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: -0.1778em;"></span><span class="mclose">]</span></span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 1em;"></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mopen"><span class="mopen">[</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: -0.1778em;"></span><span class="mopen">[</span></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.13889em;">P</span><span class="mpunct">;</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">Q</span><span class="mclose"><span class="mclose">]</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: -0.1778em;"></span><span class="mclose">]</span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mopen"><span class="mopen">[</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: -0.1778em;"></span><span class="mopen">[</span></span><span class="mord mathnormal">Q</span><span class="mclose"><span class="mclose">]</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: -0.1778em;"></span><span class="mclose">]</span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">∘</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mopen"><span class="mopen">[</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: -0.1778em;"></span><span class="mopen">[</span></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.13889em;">P</span><span class="mclose"><span class="mclose">]</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: -0.1778em;"></span><span class="mclose">]</span></span></span></span></span></span>
<p data-start="12582" data-end="12678">where <code data-start="12588" data-end="12591">⊕</code> is multiset union at the pop level and <code data-start="12631" data-end="12634">∘</code> is function composition at the field level.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>
<hr data-start="12680" data-end="12683">
<p data-start="12685" data-end="12708">If you want, I can now:</p>
<ul data-start="12710" data-end="12957" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">
<li data-start="12710" data-end="12839">
<p data-start="12712" data-end="12839"><strong data-start="12712" data-end="12749">Translate this directly into Lean</strong> (inductive types for <code data-start="12771" data-end="12777">Expr</code>, <code data-start="12779" data-end="12789">RFunExpr</code>, <code data-start="12791" data-end="12801">PopParam</code>, <code data-start="12803" data-end="12809">Proc</code>, plus <code data-start="12816" data-end="12822">step</code> and <code data-start="12827" data-end="12834">field</code>), or</p>
</li>
<li data-start="12840" data-end="12957" data-is-last-node="">
<p data-start="12842" data-end="12957" data-is-last-node=""><strong data-start="12842" data-end="12887">Give a categorical / operadic formulation</strong> where pops are generators and <code data-start="12918" data-end="12925">merge</code> is a monoidal product on modes.</p>
</li>
