<h3 data-start="1314" data-end="1339">Resulting capability:</h3>
<ul data-start="1340" data-end="1584">
<li data-start="1340" data-end="1392">
<p data-start="1342" data-end="1392">You can <strong data-start="1350" data-end="1361">compute</strong> with SpherePop syntax in Lean.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1393" data-end="1439">
<p data-start="1395" data-end="1439">You can <strong data-start="1403" data-end="1424">prove determinism</strong> of evaluation.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1440" data-end="1529">
<p data-start="1442" data-end="1529">You can <strong data-start="1450" data-end="1481">prove progress/preservation</strong> for the process calculus operational semantics.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1530" data-end="1584">
<p data-start="1532" data-end="1584">You can run <strong data-start="1544" data-end="1570">small-step simulations</strong> symbolically.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="1586" data-end="1589">
<h1 data-start="1591" data-end="1667"><strong data-start="1593" data-end="1665">Option B — Full <em data-start="1611" data-end="1629">Process Calculus</em> Mechanization (small-step proofs)</strong></h1>
<p data-start="1669" data-end="1804">This option turns the hybrid (discrete + continuous) semantics into a <strong data-start="1739" data-end="1779">proper mechanized operational system</strong>, enabling real theorems.</p>
<h3 data-start="1806" data-end="1819">Subtasks:</h3>
<ul data-start="1820" data-end="2264">
<li data-start="1820" data-end="1900">
<p data-start="1822" data-end="1900">Refine <code data-start="1829" data-end="1835">step</code> so it is well-founded and compatible with structural congruence.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1901" data-end="1945">
<p data-start="1903" data-end="1945">Add omitted symmetric rules (PAR-R, etc.).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1946" data-end="2020">
<p data-start="1948" data-end="2020">Define the <strong data-start="1959" data-end="1991">reflexive–transitive closure</strong> of <code data-start="1995" data-end="2001">step</code>, e.g. <code data-start="2008" data-end="2019">step_star</code>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2021" data-end="2264">
<p data-start="2023" data-end="2029">Prove:</p>
<ul data-start="2032" data-end="2264">
<li data-start="2032" data-end="2093">
<p data-start="2034" data-end="2093"><strong data-start="2034" data-end="2048">Congruence</strong>: <code data-start="2050" data-end="2057">P ≡ Q</code> ⇒ <code data-start="2060" data-end="2072">step (P,Π)</code> behaves identically.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2096" data-end="2146">
<p data-start="2098" data-end="2146"><strong data-start="2098" data-end="2113">Determinacy</strong> for pure pop-emission fragments.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2149" data-end="2201">
<p data-start="2151" data-end="2201"><strong data-start="2151" data-end="2165">Confluence</strong> for merge-commutative mode systems.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2204" data-end="2264">
<p data-start="2206" data-end="2264"><strong data-start="2206" data-end="2242">Subject reduction (preservation)</strong> for the typing rules.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="2266" data-end="2291">Resulting capability:</h3>
<ul data-start="2292" data-end="2413">
<li data-start="2292" data-end="2343">
<p data-start="2294" data-end="2343">A fully operational “SpherePop VM” model in Lean.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2344" data-end="2413">
<p data-start="2346" data-end="2413">Machine-checked theorems about invariants of pop emission programs.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="2415" data-end="2418">
<h1 data-start="2420" data-end="2501"><strong data-start="2422" data-end="2501">Option C — Define <em data-start="2442" data-end="2464">Continuous Semantics</em> Rigorously in Lean (hybrid system)</strong></h1>
<p data-start="2503" data-end="2550">Right now the continuous evolution is abstract:</p>
