<p data-start="2958" data-end="2972">We can encode:</p>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant="normal">Π</mi><mrow><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">Δ</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">i</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">s</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">s</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">i</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">p</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">a</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">t</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">e</mi></mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mi mathvariant="normal">Π</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mtext>  </mtext><mtext>  </mtext><mo>⊎</mo><mtext>  </mtext><mtext>  </mtext><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">m</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">e</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">r</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">g</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">e</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">_</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">p</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">a</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">i</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">r</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">s</mi></mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mi mathvariant="normal">Π</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">.</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">Π_{t+Δt} = \mathrm{dissipate}(Π_t) \;\;\uplus\;\; \mathrm{merged\_pairs}(Π_t).</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8917em; vertical-align: -0.2083em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord">Π</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3283em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span><span class="mbin mtight">+</span><span class="mord mtight">Δ</span><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2083em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathrm">dissipate</span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord">Π</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">⊎</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1.06em; vertical-align: -0.31em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathrm">merged_pairs</span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord">Π</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mord">.</span></span></span></span></span>
<h3 data-start="3060" data-end="3085">Resulting capability:</h3>
<ul data-start="3086" data-end="3231">
<li data-start="3086" data-end="3160">
<p data-start="3088" data-end="3160">The hybrid continuous–discrete nature of SpherePop becomes fully formal.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3161" data-end="3231">
<p data-start="3163" data-end="3231">One can prove <strong data-start="3177" data-end="3194">energy bounds</strong>, <strong data-start="3196" data-end="3208">locality</strong>, and <strong data-start="3214" data-end="3230">causal cones</strong>.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="3233" data-end="3236">
<h1 data-start="3238" data-end="3315"><strong data-start="3240" data-end="3315">Option D — Category-Theoretic Semantics (Operads / Monoidal Categories)</strong></h1>
<p data-start="3317" data-end="3432">This would give the <em data-start="3337" data-end="3377">high-level mathematical interpretation</em> of SpherePop, useful for RSVP theoretical integration.</p>
<h3 data-start="3434" data-end="3448">Construct:</h3>
<ul data-start="3449" data-end="3769">
<li data-start="3449" data-end="3690">
<p data-start="3451" data-end="3479">An <strong data-start="3454" data-end="3464">operad</strong> <code data-start="3465" data-end="3472">PopOp</code> where:</p>
<ul data-start="3482" data-end="3690">
<li data-start="3482" data-end="3546">
<p data-start="3484" data-end="3546">each <code data-start="3489" data-end="3492">p</code> is a generator of an operation representing emission,</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3549" data-end="3596">
<p data-start="3551" data-end="3596">parallel composition is the monoidal product,</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3599" data-end="3644">
<p data-start="3601" data-end="3644">merging is an operadic partial composition,</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3647" data-end="3690">
<p data-start="3649" data-end="3690">modes live in a <strong data-start="3665" data-end="3682">monoid object</strong> <code data-start="3683" data-end="3689">Mode</code>.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="3692" data-end="3769">
<p data-start="3694" data-end="3769">A <strong data-start="3696" data-end="3707">functor</strong> from this operad to the category of scalar fields <code data-start="3758" data-end="3768">Field(X)</code>:</p>
</li>
</ul>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi><mo>:</mo><mi>P</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>p</mi><mi>O</mi><mi>p</mi><mo>→</mo><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><mi>S</mi><mi>p</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>c</mi><mi>e</mi><mo>×</mo><mi>T</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>m</mi><mi>e</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">R</mi><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">F : PopOp \to [Space × Time, ℝ]</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.13889em;">F</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">:</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8778em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.13889em;">P</span><span class="mord mathnormal">o</span><span class="mord mathnormal">pOp</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">→</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mopen">[</span><span class="mord mathnormal">Sp</span><span class="mord mathnormal">a</span><span class="mord mathnormal">ce</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">×</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.13889em;">T</span><span class="mord mathnormal">im</span><span class="mord mathnormal">e</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord amsrm">R</span><span class="mclose">]</span></span></span></span></span>
<p data-start="3810" data-end="3818">mapping:</p>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mi>p</mi><mo>↦</mo><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>↦</mo><mi>A</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mi>δ</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">∣</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>−</mo><mi>c</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">∣</mi><mo>−</mo><mi>ρ</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">.</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">p \mapsto (x,t) \mapsto A(t) \delta(|x-c| - \rho(t)).</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.7054em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">p</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">↦</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">↦</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">A</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.03785em;">δ</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord">∣</span><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">−</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">c</span><span class="mord">∣</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">−</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">ρ</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mclose">))</span><span class="mord">.</span></span></span></span></span>
<h3 data-start="3881" data-end="3906">Resulting capability:</h3>
<ul data-start="3907" data-end="4042">
<li data-start="3907" data-end="3963">
<p data-start="3909" data-end="3963">A clean conceptual bridge to RSVP, TARTAN, HYDRA, etc.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3964" data-end="4042">
<p data-start="3966" data-end="4042">Enables deriving <strong data-start="3983" data-end="4009">topological invariants</strong> (entropy, boundary index, etc.).</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="4044" data-end="4047">
<h1 data-start="4049" data-end="4100"><strong data-start="4051" data-end="4100">Option E — Export as a real Lean file (.lean)</strong></h1>
<p data-start="4102" data-end="4115">I can output:</p>
<ul data-start="4117" data-end="4399">
<li data-start="4117" data-end="4141">
<p data-start="4119" data-end="4141">A polished Lean 4 file</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4142" data-end="4399">
<p data-start="4144" data-end="4166"><code data-start="4144" data-end="4160">spherepop.lean</code> with:</p>
<ul data-start="4169" data-end="4399">
<li data-start="4169" data-end="4181">
<p data-start="4171" data-end="4181">namespaces</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4184" data-end="4197">
<p data-start="4186" data-end="4197">definitions</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4200" data-end="4220">
<p data-start="4202" data-end="4220">imported libraries</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4223" data-end="4240">
<p data-start="4225" data-end="4240">no placeholders</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4243" data-end="4289">
<p data-start="4245" data-end="4289">full deterministic evaluation of expressions</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4292" data-end="4319">
<p data-start="4294" data-end="4319">full small-step semantics</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4322" data-end="4364">
<p data-start="4324" data-end="4364">structural congruence as a quotient type</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4367" data-end="4399">
<p data-start="4369" data-end="4399">a starting theorem environment</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="4401" data-end="4404">
<h1 data-start="4406" data-end="4477"><strong data-start="4408" data-end="4477">Option F — Define the <em data-start="4432" data-end="4456">symbolic physics layer</em> (RSVP integration)</strong></h1>
<p data-start="4479" data-end="4560">If you want SpherePop to be a <strong data-start="4509" data-end="4551">first-class syntactic fragment of RSVP</strong>, we can:</p>
<ul data-start="4562" data-end="4707">
<li data-start="4562" data-end="4688">
<p data-start="4564" data-end="4608">Add field equations for Φ derived from pops:</p>
<ul data-start="4611" data-end="4688">
<li data-start="4611" data-end="4632">
<p data-start="4613" data-end="4632">transport/diffusion</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4635" data-end="4658">
<p data-start="4637" data-end="4658">entropy evolution <code data-start="4655" data-end="4658">S</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="4661" data-end="4688">
<p data-start="4663" data-end="4688">vector field coupling <code data-start="4685" data-end="4688">v</code></p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="4689" data-end="4707">
<p data-start="4691" data-end="4707">Define functors:</p>
</li>
</ul>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">S</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">p</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">h</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">e</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">r</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">e</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">o</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">p</mi></mrow><mo>→</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">R</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">S</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">V</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">Φ</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>v</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>S</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\mathrm{SpherePop} \to \mathrm{RSVP}_{\Phi,v,S}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8889em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathrm">SpherePop</span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">→</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.9694em; vertical-align: -0.2861em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathrm">RSVP</span></span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3283em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mtight">Φ</span><span class="mpunct mtight">,</span><span class="mord mathnormal mtight" style="margin-right: 0.03588em;">v</span><span class="mpunct mtight">,</span><span class="mord mathnormal mtight" style="margin-right: 0.05764em;">S</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2861em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>
<p data-start="4764" data-end="4825">which extend the induced field to full triple-field dynamics.</p>
<p data-start="4827" data-end="4897">This would let you run <strong data-start="4850" data-end="4872">SpherePop programs</strong> as <strong data-start="4876" data-end="4896">RSVP simulations</strong>.</p>
<hr data-start="4899" data-end="4902">
<h1 data-start="4904" data-end="4947"><strong data-start="4906" data-end="4947">Tell me which option(s) you want next</strong></h1>
<p data-start="4949" data-end="4958">Examples:</p>
<ul data-start="4960" data-end="5275">
<li data-start="4960" data-end="5030">
<p data-start="4962" data-end="5030">“Give me <strong data-start="4971" data-end="4983">Option A</strong> — deterministic evaluators for expressions.”</p>
</li>
<li data-start="5031" data-end="5107">
<p data-start="5033" data-end="5107">“Do <strong data-start="5037" data-end="5049">Option B</strong> — full small-step semantics and preservation/progress.”</p>
</li>
<li data-start="5108" data-end="5171">
<p data-start="5110" data-end="5171">“Do <strong data-start="5114" data-end="5126">Option C</strong> — Lean definition of merge and dissipate.”</p>
</li>
<li data-start="5172" data-end="5226">
<p data-start="5174" data-end="5226">“Give me <strong data-start="5183" data-end="5195">Option D</strong> — the operadic formulation.”</p>
</li>
<li data-start="5227" data-end="5275">
<p data-start="5229" data-end="5275">“Export a polished <strong data-start="5248" data-end="5257">.lean</strong> file (Option E).”</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="5277" data-end="5303">You can also combine them:</p>
<blockquote data-start="5305" data-end="5342">
<p data-start="5307" data-end="5342">“Let’s do A + B now, then C later.”</p>
