bg-token-text-primary h-3 w-3 rounded-full"></div></div><div class="relative my-1 min-h-6"><div class="origin-top-start relative flex flex-col gap-2 overflow-x-clip" style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><div class="relative w-full text-start"><div class="flex w-full flex-row items-start justify-between gap-4 text-start"><button class="flex min-w-0 shrink-1 items-center gap-0.5"><span class="font-medium w-full"><span class="flex items-center gap-1 truncate text-start align-middle text-token-text-secondary hover:text-token-text-primary dark:hover:text-token-text-primary dark:text-[var(--interactive-label-tertiary-default)]" style="opacity: 1;"><div class="truncate">Thought for 33s</div></span></span></button></div></div><div class="max-w-[calc(0.8*var(--thread-content-max-width,40rem))]"></div></div></div><div data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="a53d9e73-834d-4875-a91e-dd0ada3b2218" dir="auto" class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-1-thinking"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden first:pt-[1px]"><div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full break-words dark markdown-new-styling"><p data-start="0" data-end="106">Nice, let’s level this up. For <strong data-start="31" data-end="43">Option B</strong>, I’ll turn your calculus into a proper small-step system with:</p>
<ul data-start="108" data-end="365">
<li data-start="108" data-end="157">
<p data-start="110" data-end="157">a cleaned-up <code data-start="123" data-end="129">step</code> relation (no placeholders),</p>
</li>
<li data-start="158" data-end="213">
<p data-start="160" data-end="213">structural congruence + a congruence-style step rule,</p>
</li>
<li data-start="214" data-end="259">
<p data-start="216" data-end="259">a reflexive–transitive closure <code data-start="247" data-end="258">step_star</code>,</p>
</li>
<li data-start="260" data-end="307">
<p data-start="262" data-end="307">a clear notion of “well-typed configuration”,</p>
</li>
<li data-start="308" data-end="365">
<p data-start="310" data-end="365">and <strong data-start="314" data-end="335">formal statements</strong> of preservation and progress.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="367" data-end="518">I’ll assume <strong data-start="379" data-end="391">Option A</strong>’s evaluators exist (<code data-start="412" data-end="424">eval_aexpr</code>, <code data-start="426" data-end="438">eval_bexpr</code>, <code data-start="440" data-end="454">eval_popexpr</code>) and are deterministic and total on well-typed closed programs.</p>
<p data-start="520" data-end="594">Below is a <strong data-start="531" data-end="553">drop-in refinement</strong> of the relevant parts of your spec file.</p>
<hr data-start="596" data-end="599">
