<p data-start="8192" data-end="8281">Once <code data-start="8197" data-end="8205">eval_*</code> are deterministic and total on well-typed &amp; closed terms, this is standard.</p>
<h3 data-start="8283" data-end="8299">6.2 Progress</h3>
<p data-start="8301" data-end="8400">There are several ways to formulate <strong data-start="8337" data-end="8349">progress</strong> for process calculi. A simple one in your setting:</p>
<blockquote data-start="8402" data-end="8606">
<p data-start="8404" data-end="8469"><strong data-start="8404" data-end="8417">Progress.</strong><br data-start="8417" data-end="8420">
For a closed, well-typed configuration, either:</p>
<ul data-start="8472" data-end="8606">
<li data-start="8472" data-end="8542">
<p data-start="8474" data-end="8542">the process is <code data-start="8489" data-end="8494">nil</code> modulo structural congruence (no more work), or</p>
</li>
<li data-start="8545" data-end="8606">
<p data-start="8547" data-end="8606">there exists some <code data-start="8565" data-end="8569">C'</code> and <code data-start="8574" data-end="8577">α</code> such that <code data-start="8588" data-end="8605">step env C α C'</code>.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</blockquote>
<p data-start="8608" data-end="8683">We need a notion of “closed” (no free term or process variables). For spec:</p>
