7 6.136 4.40303 6.07083 4.80371 6.03809C5.14051 6.01057 5.53708 6.00551 6.00391 6.00391C6.00551 5.53708 6.01057 5.14051 6.03809 4.80371C6.0755 4.34588 6.15483 3.94012 6.34668 3.56348L6.46875 3.34473C6.77282 2.84912 7.20856 2.44514 7.72949 2.17969L7.87207 2.11328C8.20855 1.96886 8.56979 1.90385 8.9707 1.87109C9.42091 1.83432 9.978 1.83496 10.667 1.83496H13.5C14.1891 1.83496 14.746 1.83431 15.1963 1.87109C15.6541 1.90851 16.0599 1.98788 16.4365 2.17969L16.6553 2.30176C17.151 2.60585 17.5548 3.04244 17.8203 3.56348L17.8867 3.70606C18.031 4.04235 18.0962 4.40306 18.1289 4.80371C18.1657 5.25395 18.165 5.81091 18.165 6.5V9.33301Z"></path></svg>Copy code</button></div></div></div><div class="overflow-y-auto p-4" dir="ltr"><code class="whitespace-pre! language-lean"><span>theorem progress
  (env : Env)
  {Γ : Context} {C : Config}
  (hwf : well_typed_config Γ C)
  (closed : closed_proc C.proc) :
  (∃ P', cong C.proc P' ∧ P' = Expr.Process.nil)
  ∨ (∃ α C', step env C α C') :=
begin
  -- proof outline:
  -- 1. structural induction on typing derivation of C.proc.
  -- 2. rule-by-rule analysis:
  --    - emit pe: eval_popexpr total ⇒ pop_emit step exists.
  --    - seq P Q: either P ≡ nil (then use seq_complete), or P can step.
  --    - par P Q: if either side can step, par_left or par_right applies.
  --    - if b then P else Q: eval_bexpr total ⇒ if_true/if_false step.
  --    - let x = e in P: eval_aexpr total ⇒ let_step.
  --    - fixp X P: always can do fix_step.
  -- 3. show the only stuck term is nil (modulo cong).
  admit
end
</span></code></div></div></pre>
<p data-start="9621" data-end="9742">You can refine “stuck only if nil” later to incorporate more nuanced notions of quiescence (e.g., no more pops possible).</p>
<hr data-start="9744" data-end="9747">
<h2 data-start="9749" data-end="9772">7. What you have now</h2>
<p data-start="9774" data-end="9831">Putting Options A + B together, you now effectively have:</p>
<ul data-start="9833" data-end="10155">
<li data-start="9833" data-end="9895">
<p data-start="9835" data-end="9895">A <strong data-start="9837" data-end="9863">fully-specified syntax</strong> (expressions, pops, processes).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="9896" data-end="9959">
<p data-start="9898" data-end="9959">Deterministic, total <strong data-start="9919" data-end="9933">evaluators</strong> for the expression layer.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="9960" data-end="10033">
<p data-start="9962" data-end="10033">A clear <strong data-start="9970" data-end="10006">small-step operational semantics</strong> for processes + pop-store.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="10034" data-end="10078">
<p data-start="10036" data-end="10078">A definition of <strong data-start="10052" data-end="10077">config well-typedness</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="10079" data-end="10155">
<p data-start="10081" data-end="10155">Precise <strong data-start="10089" data-end="10127">preservation and progress theorems</strong> ready to be proved in Lean.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="10157" data-end="10191">From here, natural next moves are:</p>
<ul data-start="10193" data-end="10479">
<li data-start="10193" data-end="10268">
<p data-start="10195" data-end="10268">Actually <strong data-start="10204" data-end="10226">fill in the proofs</strong> of <code data-start="10230" data-end="10244">preservation</code> and <code data-start="10249" data-end="10259">progress</code> in Lean.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="10269" data-end="10354">
<p data-start="10271" data-end="10354">Extend typing to be more informative (e.g., indexed by “closed” or “no free vars”).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="10355" data-end="10479">
<p data-start="10357" data-end="10479">Hook in the <strong data-start="10369" data-end="10393">continuous semantics</strong> (<code data-start="10395" data-end="10412">evolve_popstore</code>, <code data-start="10414" data-end="10429">induced_field</code>) and prove things like energy bounds or locality.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="10481" data-end="10507">If you’d like, next I can:</p>
<ul data-start="10509" data-end="10718" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">
<li data-start="10509" data-end="10613">
<p data-start="10511" data-end="10613">Turn this into a <strong data-start="10528" data-end="10571">single, syntactically valid Lean 4 file</strong> with missing pieces marked as <code data-start="10602" data-end="10609">sorry</code>, or</p>
</li>
<li data-start="10614" data-end="10718" data-is-last-node="">
<p data-start="10616" data-end="10718" data-is-last-node="">Start <strong data-start="10622" data-end="10643">one of the proofs</strong> (e.g., detailed preservation proof skeleton over all <code data-start="10697" data-end="10703">step</code> constructors).</p>
</li>
