# SpherePop (Lean 4) — minimal project

This repository contains a minimal Lean 4 skeleton for the **SpherePop Calculus**.
The goal is to provide a compact, compilable core you can extend with evaluators
and proofs.

## Files

- <code>lakefile.lean</code> — project definition for Lake.
- <code>src/SpherePop/Utils.lean</code> — small concrete types and helpers (Var, PVar, Point, Time, Mode, Value, Env).
- <code>src/SpherePop/Core.lean</code> — the core calculus (syntax, cong, small-step <code>step_mod</code>, typing, theorem statements).
- <code>src/SpherePop/Eval.lean</code> — placeholder evaluator predicates; replace with real evaluators.

## Build

1. Install Lean 4 and Lake.
2. Put the files in a directory and run:

<pre class="overflow-x-auto"><code>bash
lake build</code></pre>

(If you prefer <code>lean --make</code> for older setups, that may also work.)

## Next steps

- Implement <code>subst_proc</code> and <code>subst_pvar</code> concretely (capture-avoiding substitution);
- Implement deterministic evaluators in <code>Eval.lean</code> (or a dedicated evaluation module);
- Prove <code>preservation</code> and <code>progress</code> in <code>Core.lean</code> by case analysis on <code>step_mod</code>;
- Extend the calculus with the continuous <code>popstore</code> evolution semantics.

