<p data-start="2845" data-end="2879">Lean requires consistency: either:</p>
<ul data-start="2881" data-end="3075">
<li data-start="2881" data-end="2911">
<p data-start="2883" data-end="2911"><strong data-start="2883" data-end="2905">both are constants</strong>, OR</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2912" data-end="2986">
<p data-start="2914" data-end="2986"><strong data-start="2914" data-end="2931">both are defs</strong> (with the Core using <code data-start="2953" data-end="2979">namespace SpherePop.Eval</code>), OR</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2987" data-end="3075">
<p data-start="2989" data-end="3075">the Core must import the concrete definitions (but cannot declare them as <code data-start="3063" data-end="3073">constant</code>).</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="3077" data-end="3152">Currently you're doing both, which Lean will reject as duplicate constants.</p>
