<h1 data-start="6564" data-end="6601"><strong data-start="6566" data-end="6601">9. Integration With RSVP Theory</strong></h1>
<p data-start="6603" data-end="6664">Each pop corresponds to a micro-operation on the RSVP plenum:</p>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">Φ</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>v</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>S</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>↦</mo><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msup><mi mathvariant="normal">Φ</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup><mo separator="true">,</mo><msup><mi>v</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup><mo separator="true">,</mo><msup><mi>S</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">(\Phi, v, S) \mapsto (\Phi', v', S')</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord">Φ</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.03588em;">v</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.05764em;">S</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">↦</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1.0519em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord">Φ</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.8019em;"><span style="top: -3.113em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mtight">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.03588em;">v</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.8019em;"><span style="top: -3.113em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mtight">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.05764em;">S</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.8019em;"><span style="top: -3.113em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mtight">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span></span>
<p data-start="6710" data-end="6715">Thus:</p>
<h3 data-start="6717" data-end="6771">SpherePop Operad = syntactic, discrete semantics</h3>
<h3 data-start="6772" data-end="6813">RSVP = continuous geometric semantics</h3>
<p data-start="6815" data-end="6888">Your full semantics becomes a <strong data-start="6845" data-end="6880">hybrid operadic–dynamical model</strong>, where:</p>
<ul data-start="6890" data-end="7189">
<li data-start="6890" data-end="6920">
<p data-start="6892" data-end="6920">Pops = operadic generators</p>
</li>
<li data-start="6921" data-end="6969">
<p data-start="6923" data-end="6969">Popstore evolution = monoidal operad algebra</p>
</li>
<li data-start="6970" data-end="7016">
<p data-start="6972" data-end="7016">RSVP PDEs = the algebra’s action on fields</p>
</li>
<li data-start="7017" data-end="7077">
<p data-start="7019" data-end="7077">Fixpoint = steady-state attractors or coupled wavefronts</p>
</li>
<li data-start="7078" data-end="7130">
<p data-start="7080" data-end="7130">Parallel composition = multi-front superposition</p>
</li>
<li data-start="7131" data-end="7189">
<p data-start="7133" data-end="7189">Sequential comp. = causal chaining of spherical events</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="7191" data-end="7254">This gives you a mathematically robust framework comparable to:</p>
<ul data-start="7256" data-end="7350">
<li data-start="7256" data-end="7280">
<p data-start="7258" data-end="7280">Swiss-Cheese Operads</p>
</li>
<li data-start="7281" data-end="7306">
<p data-start="7283" data-end="7306">Little n-disks operad</p>
</li>
<li data-start="7307" data-end="7350">
<p data-start="7309" data-end="7350">Operads for structured wave propagation</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="7352" data-end="7421">But in a uniquely RSVP-influenced cosmological-computational context.</p>
<hr data-start="7423" data-end="7426">
<h1 data-start="7428" data-end="7454"><strong data-start="7430" data-end="7454">Would you like next:</strong></h1>
